<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/4d6965a6d7e141308ba116d3ac38fe5f.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 4 and A = 10 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>22.7</li><li>23.0</li><li>80.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({10}\right)}}}=\frac{{4}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{4}}{{\tan{{\left({10}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{22.685127278471}\approx{22.7}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={4}^{{2}}+{22.685127278471}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={16}+{514.61499964042}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={530.61499964042}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{530.61499964042}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{23.035081932575}\approx{23}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{10}^{\circ}\approx{80}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

